extracted_text: A residential district allowing a minimum of 10,000 square feet if public water and sewer facilities are available or 15,000 square feet if only public water or only sewer facilities are available and 20,000 square feet if neither service is available.
llm_outputs.rationale: This text describes the minimum lot sizes for the R-10 Residential District based on availability of public water and sewer services. However, it does not provide a single definitive minimum lot size value.
llm_outputs.answer: 10,000 sq ft (with public water and sewer); 15,000 sq ft (with only public water or only sewer); 20,000 sq ft (without public water and sewer)
